quotas.name: MP Private Seats - Open Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : MP Private Seats - Open Quota**

Local resident (native resident) of Madhya Pradesh. In case local residents are not available, then other state candidates are considered
Local Resident-Any one of the below criteria
1) Born in Madhya Pradesh
2) Continuoulsy residing in MP for the last 10 years
3) Serving /retired employee of the State Govt Corporation / Board / Commission under the State Government but if the entity is located outside the State of MP then 1 or 2 is required.
4) AIS officer allotted to MP cadre
5) Statutory or constitutional post appointed to the state of MP
6) Exservicemen resided in MP for 5 years or their family members are already residing in MP
There is one more clause in the format mentioning Central Govt Employees-check that too. Next of kin of all the above (husbands, mother, father of exservicemen concerned)

quotas.name: MP Private Seats - NRI Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : MP Private Seats - NRI Quota**

1. MP Docimile NRI/OCI Candidates as per SC order. However first degree cousins are missing in the NRI OCI affidavit.
2. If MP Domicile candidates are not available then other state candidates are eligible

**Eligibility for the Quota : MP Private Seats - Open Quota**

Local resident (native resident) of Madhya Pradesh. In case local residents are not available, then other state candidates are considered
Local Resident-Any one of the below criteria
1) Born in Madhya Pradesh
2) Continuoulsy residing in MP for the last 10 years
3) Serving /retired employee of the State Govt Corporation / Board / Commission under the State Government but if the entity is located outside the State of MP then 1 or 2 is required.
4) AIS officer allotted to MP cadre
5) Statutory or constitutional post appointed to the state of MP
6) Exservicemen resided in MP for 5 years or their family members are already residing in MP
There is one more clause in the format mentioning Central Govt Employees-check that too. Next of kin of all the above (husbands, mother, father of exservicemen concerned)

quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : MP Private Seats - Open Quota**

Local resident (native resident) of Madhya Pradesh. In case local residents are not available, then other state candidates are considered
Local Resident-Any one of the below criteria
1) Born in Madhya Pradesh
2) Continuoulsy residing in MP for the last 10 years
3) Serving /retired employee of the State Govt Corporation / Board / Commission under the State Government but if the entity is located outside the State of MP then 1 or 2 is required.
4) AIS officer allotted to MP cadre
5) Statutory or constitutional post appointed to the state of MP
6) Exservicemen resided in MP for 5 years or their family members are already residing in MP
There is one more clause in the format mentioning Central Govt Employees-check that too. Next of kin of all the above (husbands, mother, father of exservicemen concerned)

**Local resident (native resident) of Madhya Pradesh. In case local**

Residents are not available, <u>then other state candidates are considered</u>

Local Resident-Any one of the below criteria
1. Born in Madhya Pradesh
2. Continuoulsy residing in MP for the last 10 years
3. Serving /retired employee of the State Govt Corporation / Board / Commission under the State Government but if the entity is located outside the State of MP then 1. or 2. is required
4. AIS officer allotted to MP cadre
5. Statutory or constitutional post appointed to the state of MP
6. Exservicemen resided in MP for 5 years or their family members are already residing in MP.  

There is one more clause in the format mentioning Central Govt Employees-check that too. Next of kin of all the above (husbands, mother, father of exservicemen concerned)
